		<category><![CDATA[what to do in rio de janeiro]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://indietravelpodcast.com/?p=5427</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>The Rio de Janeiro Botanical Garden is a great place to visit on a hot day to get away from the noise and the crowds. There are thousands of different plants, and lots of little surprises in various parts of the park.</p><p><a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/brazil/rio-de-janeiro-botanical-gardens-brazil-video/">Rio de Janeiro Botanical Garden, Brazil</a> by <a rel="author" href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/author/linda/">Linda Martin</a> was originally published on <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/">Indie Travel Podcast</a> (<a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/itunes">find in iTunes</a>). They also have <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/books/">travel books</a> and guides to <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/asia/">Asia</a>, <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/europe/">Europe</a>, <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/oceania/">Oceania</a>, <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/south-america/">South America</a>, and more.</p>]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The Rio de Janeiro Botanical Garden is a great place to visit on a hot day to get away from the noise and the crowds. There are thousands of different plants, and lots of little surprises like waterfalls and stone structures in various parts of the park.</p>
<p>The park was founded in 1808 by the Prince Regent of the time, who was later John VI of Portugal. He also founded a gunpowder factory on the site, which produced most of Brazil&#8217;s gunpowder and still stands as a museum today. </p>
<p>Entrance is six reals, well worth the investment &#8212; but be aware that the garden closes at five pm &#8212; get there early to get the most out of the day.</p>
<p><iframe width="599" height="337" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/PVroIDVltrc?fs=1&#038;feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
<p><em>For more on Brazil, check out our <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/south-america/brazil/">Brazil country page</a>.</em></p>
<p><a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/brazil/rio-de-janeiro-botanical-gardens-brazil-video/">Rio de Janeiro Botanical Garden, Brazil</a> by <a rel="author" href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/author/linda/">Linda Martin</a> was originally published on <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/">Indie Travel Podcast</a> (<a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/itunes">find in iTunes</a>). They also have <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/books/">travel books</a> and guides to <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/asia/">Asia</a>, <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/europe/">Europe</a>, <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/oceania/">Oceania</a>, <a href="http://indietravelpodcast.com/south-america/">South America</a>, and more.</p>]]></content:encoded>
